WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.863 --> 00:00:03.549
What are the chances

2
00:00:03.573 --> 00:00:05.718
my van hits a police car this morning?

3
00:00:05.742 --> 00:00:07.094
You gonna help me.

4
00:00:07.118 --> 00:00:09.263
Odell Morgan. What can you tell me?

5
00:00:09.287 --> 00:00:10.848
He was convicted of
killing his wife. Simone.

6
00:00:10.872 --> 00:00:12.183
Simone's body was never found.

7
00:00:12.207 --> 00:00:14.894
I did not kill my wife.

8
00:00:14.918 --> 00:00:17.104
Morgan's brother-in-law testified

9
00:00:17.128 --> 00:00:19.106
to seeing Morgan transporting
a heavy rug into his vehicle.

10
00:00:19.130 --> 00:00:20.775
Why did you lie?

11
00:00:20.799 --> 00:00:22.068
I had to.

12
00:00:22.092 --> 00:00:24.070
- They made me.
- Who are you scared of?

13
00:00:24.094 --> 00:00:25.404
Someone took him out.

14
00:00:26.721 --> 00:00:28.705
Someone framed Morgan.

15
00:00:30.350 --> 00:00:32.078
Wanna know who killed my wife.

16
00:00:34.145 --> 00:00:35.790
Your dad didn't kill her.

17
00:00:35.814 --> 00:00:37.291
Who did?

18
00:00:37.315 --> 00:00:39.669
I don't know yet. but I'm gonna help.

19
00:00:43.071 --> 00:00:45.550
What are the chances

20
00:00:45.574 --> 00:00:48.952
that I crashed into you?

21
00:01:00.046 --> 00:01:01.440
Oh. you're still here.

22
00:01:01.464 --> 00:01:03.442
I thought everyone cleared out.

23
00:01:03.466 --> 00:01:05.069
I'm looking for a new office phone.

24
00:01:05.093 --> 00:01:07.947
- Mine has gone paws up.
- In there.

25
00:01:07.971 --> 00:01:09.723
Okay.

26
00:01:20.775 --> 00:01:22.420
Simone Morgan's case.

27
00:01:22.444 --> 00:01:24.255
Anything pop?

28
00:01:24.279 --> 00:01:25.590
No.

29
00:01:25.614 --> 00:01:28.217
The more I spend on it.
the more I realize

30
00:01:28.241 --> 00:01:30.970
I keep running into the same questions.

31
00:01:30.994 --> 00:01:33.347
Cold cases always feel like that.

32
00:01:33.371 --> 00:01:35.808
Working them is an act of faith.

33
00:01:36.398 --> 00:01:38.603
Yeah. you gotta blindly
believe that someday. somehow.

34
00:01:38.627 --> 00:01:40.527
something will appear.

35
00:01:41.364 --> 00:01:42.699
A lead that was missed.

36
00:01:46.074 --> 00:01:47.743
You want help?

37
00:01:48.803 --> 00:01:50.986
Voight said I can't have
anyone helping me

38
00:01:51.010 --> 00:01:53.117
until something new pops.

39
00:01:53.141 --> 00:01:55.042
So we'll work it off hours.

40
00:01:55.936 --> 00:01:57.788
That's okay. You don't have to do that.

41
00:01:57.812 --> 00:01:59.523
You could just say thank you and let me.

42
00:02:02.484 --> 00:02:04.170
Thank you.

43
00:02:04.194 --> 00:02:05.320
Mm-hmm.

44
00:02:09.533 --> 00:02:10.843
Timeline?

45
00:02:10.867 --> 00:02:12.428
I'm working the last 36 hours

46
00:02:12.452 --> 00:02:13.971
before Simone died.

47
00:02:13.995 --> 00:02:17.522
She used to work the night
shift at a local diner.

48
00:02:18.690 --> 00:02:20.478
She worked there
the night before she died?

49
00:02:20.502 --> 00:02:21.651
Yeah.

50
00:02:22.045 --> 00:02:23.064
Typical night.

51
00:02:23.088 --> 00:02:24.607
Clocked out at 11:02 p.m.

52
00:02:24.631 --> 00:02:26.025
Walked home.

53
00:02:28.260 --> 00:02:30.029
She always took the same path home.

54
00:02:30.053 --> 00:02:32.031
It's about an 18-minute walk.

55
00:02:47.612 --> 00:02:49.423
And she made it home. no problem.

56
00:02:49.447 --> 00:02:52.093
Yes. but she didn't go to sleep.

57
00:02:52.117 --> 00:02:54.971
Instead. she stayed up
and placed three 911 calls.

58
00:02:54.995 --> 00:02:56.013
all hang-ups.

59
00:02:56.037 --> 00:02:57.604
Any theories why?

60
00:02:58.540 --> 00:03:01.102
Original detectives thought
the 911 calls were related

61
00:03:01.126 --> 00:03:03.271
to her husband.
that they had been fighting.

62
00:03:03.295 --> 00:03:05.904
she was scared.
but we know that's not true.

63
00:03:13.638 --> 00:03:15.032
Then she wakes up the next day.

64
00:03:15.056 --> 00:03:16.267
stays home with her kid.

65
00:03:16.291 --> 00:03:18.619
takes her kid to a sleepover
at the friend's.

66
00:03:18.643 --> 00:03:20.663
Then doesn't go to work.

67
00:03:20.687 --> 00:03:23.332
Her and Odell go
to a bar instead. fight.

68
00:03:23.356 --> 00:03:25.877
He can tell something's wrong.
She seems off.

69
00:03:25.901 --> 00:03:27.712
They go home. He passes out.

70
00:03:27.736 --> 00:03:29.338
And wakes up to blood.

71
00:03:29.362 --> 00:03:32.008
Her body's gone.
but the amount of blood loss

72
00:03:32.032 --> 00:03:33.843
indicates death.

73
00:03:33.867 --> 00:03:35.720
And someone frames
Odell Morgan for her death.

74
00:03:35.744 --> 00:03:37.805
then years later. kills Carter
Thomas to cover their tracks.

75
00:03:37.829 --> 00:03:40.456
Something happened to her
in those 36 hours.

76
00:03:40.480 --> 00:03:42.018
She was fine at work. She goes home.

77
00:03:42.042 --> 00:03:43.269
She calls 911.

78
00:03:43.293 --> 00:03:44.645
Acts strange. stays home all day.

79
00:03:44.669 --> 00:03:46.480
calls out of work.
fights with her husband.

80
00:03:46.504 --> 00:03:47.964
Is killed.

81
00:03:50.842 --> 00:03:53.428
Feels like she was scared of something.

82
00:03:55.364 --> 00:03:58.367
I really don't remember
my mom being scared.

83
00:04:01.102 --> 00:04:03.670
Why are we walking this way again?

84
00:04:04.731 --> 00:04:06.673
Repetition.

85
00:04:06.942 --> 00:04:09.092
Might help jog the memory.

86
00:04:09.861 --> 00:04:13.430
I told you. I don't really
remember anything.

87
00:04:14.032 --> 00:04:15.932
I wasn't paying attention.

88
00:04:16.243 --> 00:04:17.809
You were 15.

89
00:04:18.758 --> 00:04:20.009
Of course you weren't.

90
00:04:21.790 --> 00:04:24.227
Do you remember her
being off the next day

91
00:04:24.251 --> 00:04:26.401
or her mentioning anything?

92
00:04:27.128 --> 00:04:30.113
No. I don't.

93
00:04:31.406 --> 00:04:33.569
I don't know. I'm sorry.

94
00:04:33.593 --> 00:04:35.702
There's no reason to be sorry.

95
00:04:36.846 --> 00:04:38.157
What could have happened to her?

96
00:04:38.181 --> 00:04:42.686
I mean. something that
she was murdered over?

97
00:04:48.131 --> 00:04:49.466
What?

98
00:04:50.277 --> 00:04:51.718
What is it?

99
00:04:52.487 --> 00:04:54.596
I didn't notice that before.

100
00:04:55.949 --> 00:04:57.426
A truck driver named Noah Lewis

101
00:04:57.450 --> 00:04:59.929
was shot in the chest
on that block six years ago.

102
00:04:59.953 --> 00:05:01.889
A murder.

103
00:05:01.913 --> 00:05:03.307
What date?

104
00:05:03.331 --> 00:05:04.731
Mm...

105
00:05:05.625 --> 00:05:07.436
August 22nd.

106
00:05:07.460 --> 00:05:08.563
The night before Simone was killed.

107
00:05:08.587 --> 00:05:09.856
What time?

108
00:05:11.715 --> 00:05:13.359
Uh. gunshots were reported to 911

109
00:05:13.383 --> 00:05:16.362
from a nearby neighbor at 11:07 p.m.

110
00:05:16.386 --> 00:05:17.905
Right when Simone was walking home.

111
00:05:17.929 --> 00:05:19.156
She passed that location.

112
00:05:19.180 --> 00:05:20.515
Every single night.

113
00:05:23.518 --> 00:05:25.353
What if that's why she was killed?

114
00:05:28.023 --> 00:05:29.923
She witnessed a murder.

115
00:05:36.123 --> 00:05:38.066
The night before
Simone Morgan was killed.

116
00:05:38.080 --> 00:05:39.912
a young truck driver
named Noah Lewis was

117
00:05:39.936 --> 00:05:42.077
shot and killed in a suspected
drug rip gone wrong.

118
00:05:42.101 --> 00:05:43.662
Police thought it was a rip crew.

119
00:05:43.686 --> 00:05:44.788
but they never confirmed it.

120
00:05:44.812 --> 00:05:46.373
because Noah's killer was never caught.

121
00:05:46.397 --> 00:05:48.292
How is this related to Simone's murder?

122
00:05:48.316 --> 00:05:50.419
Noah's time of death is
consistent with the exact time

123
00:05:50.443 --> 00:05:52.421
Simone would have been walking home.

124
00:05:52.445 --> 00:05:54.840
And her usual route puts her
in the exact spot

125
00:05:54.864 --> 00:05:56.466
where Noah was murdered.

126
00:05:56.490 --> 00:05:58.969
We believe that
Simone witnessed the homicide.

127
00:05:58.993 --> 00:06:00.971
- Hmm.
- Okay.

128
00:06:00.995 --> 00:06:04.975
So your theory is.
Simone saw Noah get murdered.

129
00:06:04.999 --> 00:06:06.393
Offender clocked her. tracked her down.

130
00:06:06.417 --> 00:06:07.436
and then killed her too?

131
00:06:07.460 --> 00:06:09.062
- And Carter.
- Yes.

132
00:06:09.086 --> 00:06:10.772
Offender was covering his tracks.

133
00:06:10.796 --> 00:06:12.649
I mean. it's wide. but it could fit.

134
00:06:12.673 --> 00:06:13.901
It fits.

135
00:06:13.925 --> 00:06:15.110
Why Simone was scared.

136
00:06:15.134 --> 00:06:16.445
Why she acted off the next day.

137
00:06:16.469 --> 00:06:19.031
Why she called 911. called in sick.

138
00:06:19.055 --> 00:06:21.831
She didn't know what to do.
She was panicking.

139
00:06:22.475 --> 00:06:24.703
If we're right. we ID who killed Noah.

140
00:06:24.727 --> 00:06:26.896
then we ID who killed Simone.

141
00:06:30.399 --> 00:06:32.044
It's good.

142
00:06:32.068 --> 00:06:33.342
It's enough now.

143
00:06:35.571 --> 00:06:37.299
Come on. let's all work it.

144
00:06:37.323 --> 00:06:39.885
Noah was found shot
beside his box truck.

145
00:06:39.909 --> 00:06:42.846
The truck was modified
to conceal bulk narcotics.

146
00:06:42.870 --> 00:06:45.265
and the traps were forced open
and empty of drugs

147
00:06:45.289 --> 00:06:46.934
by the time police arrived on scene.

148
00:06:46.958 --> 00:06:48.769
So was Noah affiliated?

149
00:06:48.793 --> 00:06:51.355
Yeah. documented G-Park.

150
00:06:51.379 --> 00:06:53.232
DEA had his truck indexed.

151
00:06:53.256 --> 00:06:55.609
Electronic homicide file
was pretty thin.

152
00:06:55.633 --> 00:06:57.236
None of the handwritten
GPRs were in there.

153
00:06:57.260 --> 00:06:59.947
Yeah. but originals should
still be with the Area Cold Case.

154
00:06:59.971 --> 00:07:01.490
Yep. Area 1.

155
00:07:01.514 --> 00:07:02.997
I'll be back.

156
00:07:03.891 --> 00:07:06.018
You think that's why she was killed?

157
00:07:07.478 --> 00:07:09.331
She witnessed a murder?

158
00:07:09.355 --> 00:07:11.839
Do you remember hearing
the name Noah Lewis?

159
00:07:12.692 --> 00:07:15.259
No. I don't think so.

160
00:07:19.782 --> 00:07:21.307
This is him.

161
00:07:22.526 --> 00:07:24.361
Do you recognize him?

162
00:07:25.997 --> 00:07:27.498
No.

163
00:07:29.667 --> 00:07:31.937
My mom saw this kid die?

164
00:07:31.961 --> 00:07:35.148
That's so awful.
I mean. she must have been terrified.

165
00:07:35.172 --> 00:07:39.027
It's still just a theory.
but it feels good to me.

166
00:07:39.051 --> 00:07:40.219
Good?

167
00:07:41.596 --> 00:07:42.828
Right.

168
00:07:43.870 --> 00:07:45.329
It feels right.

169
00:07:48.853 --> 00:07:50.455
Hey. sorry.

170
00:07:50.479 --> 00:07:52.249
Uh. lead detective on Noah's case

171
00:07:52.273 --> 00:07:54.042
died from cancer last year.

172
00:07:54.066 --> 00:07:55.544
but all the files are in Area 1.

173
00:07:55.568 --> 00:07:57.004
so I told them we'd be coming by.

174
00:07:57.028 --> 00:07:58.654
All right. Thank you.

175
00:08:04.368 --> 00:08:08.932
Look. um. I gotta go.

176
00:08:08.956 --> 00:08:10.350
I'll call you as soon as I know more.

177
00:08:10.374 --> 00:08:12.191
You can call me anytime.

178
00:08:13.516 --> 00:08:14.684
Okay.

179
00:08:22.678 --> 00:08:24.745
All these unsolved murders.

180
00:08:25.598 --> 00:08:27.367
Families without closure.

181
00:08:27.391 --> 00:08:28.702
Yeah.

182
00:08:28.726 --> 00:08:30.287
Most of these people spend
their whole lives

183
00:08:30.311 --> 00:08:31.872
waiting for answers they'll never get.

184
00:08:31.896 --> 00:08:33.540
And this is just Area 1.

185
00:08:33.564 --> 00:08:34.857
This way.

186
00:08:37.443 --> 00:08:40.947
Should be here.

187
00:08:44.325 --> 00:08:45.785
Here. take this one.

188
00:08:54.085 --> 00:08:55.586
Okay.

189
00:09:06.055 --> 00:09:08.080
The handwritten notes here.

190
00:09:10.915 --> 00:09:12.375
Person of interest log.

191
00:09:17.567 --> 00:09:19.068
Lead detective was thorough.

192
00:09:21.051 --> 00:09:22.381
Noted every person he spoke to.

193
00:09:22.405 --> 00:09:23.990
even the ones that went nowhere.

194
00:09:31.998 --> 00:09:33.499
Hey. can you read this?

195
00:09:37.670 --> 00:09:42.008
Looks like "talk to Marcus again."

196
00:09:43.467 --> 00:09:45.075
Who's Marcus?

197
00:09:45.678 --> 00:09:46.989
I don't know. there's...

198
00:09:47.013 --> 00:09:49.074
there's a bunch of Marcuses listed here.

199
00:09:49.098 --> 00:09:50.581
Let me see.

200
00:09:51.350 --> 00:09:55.414
The lead detective might
be dead. but chances are.

201
00:09:55.438 --> 00:09:58.190
he hooked in the reporting
officer assigned to the beat.

202
00:10:03.375 --> 00:10:04.835
Brian Foster.

203
00:10:06.365 --> 00:10:08.719
- Detective Foster.
- Yeah.

204
00:10:14.498 --> 00:10:15.809
Torres. Intelligence.

205
00:10:15.833 --> 00:10:17.477
Oh. hey. Voight's guys.

206
00:10:17.501 --> 00:10:19.354
- Imani.
- Uh. listen.

207
00:10:19.378 --> 00:10:21.690
This poor bastard got
choked out in broad daylight.

208
00:10:21.714 --> 00:10:23.692
I got six witnesses; they're all high.

209
00:10:23.716 --> 00:10:25.152
So I can give you five minutes.

210
00:10:25.176 --> 00:10:26.153
Good?

211
00:10:26.177 --> 00:10:27.237
Mind?

212
00:10:27.261 --> 00:10:28.822
People get all weird these days.

213
00:10:28.846 --> 00:10:30.782
So we're looking into
the Noah Lewis case.

214
00:10:30.806 --> 00:10:32.451
It's a truck driver that got shot and...

215
00:10:32.475 --> 00:10:36.246
Yeah. was whacked outside
his truck in Bronzeville?

216
00:10:36.270 --> 00:10:37.748
Yeah. I remember it.

217
00:10:37.772 --> 00:10:38.790
I was assigned to that beat back then.

218
00:10:38.814 --> 00:10:40.459
It was a dope rip gone wrong.

219
00:10:40.483 --> 00:10:41.460
Kid was young.

220
00:10:41.484 --> 00:10:43.175
Was a damn shame.

221
00:10:43.694 --> 00:10:45.321
Yeah. are these your notes?

222
00:10:46.489 --> 00:10:48.217
Yeah. that's my handwriting.

223
00:10:48.241 --> 00:10:50.886
I was first officer on scene
that night. did the paper.

224
00:10:50.910 --> 00:10:53.347
Do you recall who Marcus was?

225
00:10:53.371 --> 00:10:55.807
Uh. "talk to Marcus again."

226
00:10:55.831 --> 00:10:58.060
No. I don't remember any Marcus.

227
00:10:58.084 --> 00:11:00.312
What the hell are you guys
doing with that old case anyway?

228
00:11:00.336 --> 00:11:01.522
Well. we believe Noah Lewis has

229
00:11:01.546 --> 00:11:03.232
a connection with two other homicides.

230
00:11:03.256 --> 00:11:05.442
Simone Morgan and Carter Thomas.

231
00:11:05.466 --> 00:11:06.944
Yeah. never heard of them.

232
00:11:06.968 --> 00:11:08.529
but I appreciate the commitment.

233
00:11:08.553 --> 00:11:10.572
All right? Been there before myself.

234
00:11:10.596 --> 00:11:12.157
Locked in on a case that went nowhere.

235
00:11:12.181 --> 00:11:14.952
So no idea who this Marcus was

236
00:11:14.976 --> 00:11:16.495
or why you wanted to speak to him again?

237
00:11:16.519 --> 00:11:17.955
Nah. sorry.

238
00:11:17.979 --> 00:11:19.456
You know. we interviewed
dozens of G-Park Lords.

239
00:11:19.480 --> 00:11:20.707
No one said a thing.

240
00:11:20.731 --> 00:11:22.209
They closed rank. right?

241
00:11:22.233 --> 00:11:24.294
Seemed like they...
they knew who committed the rip

242
00:11:24.318 --> 00:11:25.611
and wanted street justice.

243
00:11:27.446 --> 00:11:28.465
Did they get it?

244
00:11:28.489 --> 00:11:29.967
Probably.

245
00:11:29.991 --> 00:11:31.385
I mean. chances are.
whoever killed that poor kid

246
00:11:31.409 --> 00:11:32.553
is long dead and buried

247
00:11:32.577 --> 00:11:33.887
at the bottom of a lake somewhere.

248
00:11:33.911 --> 00:11:35.013
Right.

249
00:11:36.289 --> 00:11:38.100
I gotta go. but any other questions

250
00:11:38.124 --> 00:11:39.940
come up. you just give me a holler. hmm?

251
00:11:40.543 --> 00:11:42.062
- All right. Thank you.
- Thank you for your time.

252
00:11:42.086 --> 00:11:44.106
Mm-hmm.

253
00:11:46.883 --> 00:11:48.301
Dante. you got ears on?

254
00:11:51.220 --> 00:11:52.656
Yeah. go ahead.

255
00:11:52.680 --> 00:11:54.616
I ran all the Marcuses you gave me.
I got one possible.

256
00:11:54.640 --> 00:11:56.827
His name is Marcus Lee.

257
00:11:56.851 --> 00:11:58.328
He's listed in the gang database

258
00:11:58.352 --> 00:11:59.746
and your personal logbook.

259
00:11:59.770 --> 00:12:01.915
He was in the G-Park six years ago.

260
00:12:01.939 --> 00:12:04.459
Young. but listed as
an enforcer for their runners.

261
00:12:04.483 --> 00:12:05.544
All right. that fits.

262
00:12:05.568 --> 00:12:06.712
Uh. what's his status?

263
00:12:06.736 --> 00:12:08.463
Uh. he got no status now.

264
00:12:08.487 --> 00:12:10.716
The G-Parks cut ties 'cause
he got high off his own supply.

265
00:12:10.740 --> 00:12:11.967
He's been arrested multiple times

266
00:12:11.991 --> 00:12:14.094
for possession and solicitation.

267
00:12:14.118 --> 00:12:15.095
So he might talk now?

268
00:12:15.119 --> 00:12:16.305
Yeah.

269
00:12:16.329 --> 00:12:18.307
His LKA was knocked down two years ago.

270
00:12:18.331 --> 00:12:20.976
but he's known to work
an old lot on 16th and Cicero.

271
00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:22.524
Could be worth a shot.

272
00:12:27.340 --> 00:12:29.234
Approaching the back door now.

273
00:12:29.258 --> 00:12:31.820
Copy you. Ocean. We got your six.

274
00:13:19.433 --> 00:13:20.433
Here we go.

275
00:13:24.480 --> 00:13:26.130
What's up. man?

276
00:13:27.191 --> 00:13:28.502
Who you talking to?

277
00:13:28.526 --> 00:13:29.628
I'm talking to you. man.

278
00:13:29.652 --> 00:13:30.963
I'm looking at you.

279
00:13:30.987 --> 00:13:32.923
Oh. you friendly now. huh?

280
00:13:32.947 --> 00:13:34.883
Well. I ain't. so keep it
pushing with your friendly ass.

281
00:13:34.907 --> 00:13:36.260
Wanna be friends now?

282
00:13:36.284 --> 00:13:38.136
Got some good dope.

283
00:13:38.160 --> 00:13:40.496
Show me what you got.
I'll give you a good deal.

284
00:13:45.232 --> 00:13:46.603
Who the hell are you

285
00:13:46.627 --> 00:13:47.813
and why the hell you think
you can sling here?

286
00:13:47.837 --> 00:13:49.106
Chill. bro.

287
00:13:49.130 --> 00:13:50.607
I'ma show you how chill I get.

288
00:13:50.631 --> 00:13:52.341
Let's go get him.

289
00:14:00.308 --> 00:14:02.202
Don't move! Hey!

290
00:14:02.226 --> 00:14:04.663
I got one in custody.
Target took off to the south side

291
00:14:04.687 --> 00:14:05.664
of the building wearing a gray shirt.

292
00:14:05.688 --> 00:14:06.623
Chicago PD.

293
00:14:06.647 --> 00:14:07.708
Hey. stop!

294
00:14:07.732 --> 00:14:09.251
Stop.

295
00:14:11.193 --> 00:14:13.297
Stop. stop moving.

296
00:14:13.321 --> 00:14:14.506
Put your hands out.

297
00:14:14.530 --> 00:14:15.591
Calm your ass down.

298
00:14:15.615 --> 00:14:16.699
We got you now.

299
00:14:23.370 --> 00:14:25.139
2019?

300
00:14:25.163 --> 00:14:26.849
You asking me about
something from six years ago?

301
00:14:26.873 --> 00:14:28.267
What's the statute of limitations?

302
00:14:28.291 --> 00:14:30.103
We know you were with the G-Parks then.

303
00:14:30.127 --> 00:14:32.146
We know you were
overseeing their runners.

304
00:14:32.170 --> 00:14:34.065
One of them was Noah Lewis.

305
00:14:34.089 --> 00:14:35.233
I told you. I don't know who Noah is.

306
00:14:35.257 --> 00:14:36.609
And I told you. I don't believe you.

307
00:14:36.633 --> 00:14:38.111
It was years ago.

308
00:14:38.135 --> 00:14:39.779
I don't even remember
who I was back then.

309
00:14:39.803 --> 00:14:41.030
There's not much standing between you

310
00:14:41.054 --> 00:14:42.156
and getting out of here.

311
00:14:42.180 --> 00:14:43.658
but we got 48 hours to hold you.

312
00:14:43.682 --> 00:14:45.957
That is a long time to go
before you're getting well.

313
00:14:46.685 --> 00:14:48.121
It was August 22nd.

314
00:14:48.145 --> 00:14:49.622
Someone ripped off
Noah's truck and killed him.

315
00:14:49.646 --> 00:14:50.731
Who?

316
00:14:52.858 --> 00:14:55.837
You helping right now could
help solve three murders.

317
00:14:55.861 --> 00:14:57.130
You said three?

318
00:14:57.154 --> 00:14:58.548
Whoever killed that young truck driver

319
00:14:58.572 --> 00:15:00.174
also killed two other people.

320
00:15:00.198 --> 00:15:01.533
one of them a young mother.

321
00:15:06.621 --> 00:15:08.016
Listen.

322
00:15:08.040 --> 00:15:09.517
You're down on your luck right now.

323
00:15:09.541 --> 00:15:11.269
You're feeling sick. useless.

324
00:15:11.293 --> 00:15:12.448
I get it.

325
00:15:12.472 --> 00:15:14.564
But I promise you.
right now. you're not.

326
00:15:14.588 --> 00:15:16.696
Right now. you can help.

327
00:15:17.462 --> 00:15:19.381
And I won't forget it.

328
00:15:22.637 --> 00:15:23.948
That old rip was an inside job.

329
00:15:23.972 --> 00:15:25.783
I thought that then. I think that now.

330
00:15:25.807 --> 00:15:27.285
An inside job by the G-Parks?

331
00:15:27.309 --> 00:15:28.411
Yeah. man. that's what I'm saying.

332
00:15:28.435 --> 00:15:29.871
Okay. why do you think that?

333
00:15:29.895 --> 00:15:31.789
The G-Parks was a mess back then.

334
00:15:31.813 --> 00:15:34.625
- Okay.
- Fighting. beefing.

335
00:15:34.649 --> 00:15:36.883
There was this one guy who was shut out

336
00:15:37.694 --> 00:15:40.048
because he kept slipping up. kept lying.

337
00:15:40.072 --> 00:15:41.721
Okay. Who?

338
00:15:43.037 --> 00:15:44.789
We need a name.

339
00:15:47.913 --> 00:15:49.265
Darrell Jenkins.

340
00:15:49.289 --> 00:15:50.600
Long rap. mostly armed robbery

341
00:15:50.624 --> 00:15:52.018
and aggravated assault.

342
00:15:52.042 --> 00:15:53.603
He was with the G-Parks
since he was a teenager.

343
00:15:53.627 --> 00:15:55.396
Now. Marcus's story checks out.

344
00:15:55.420 --> 00:15:57.899
Darrell was beefing
with the higher-ups in 2019.

345
00:15:57.923 --> 00:15:59.484
and we got Gang Intel's evidence

346
00:15:59.508 --> 00:16:00.860
and text records of it.

347
00:16:00.884 --> 00:16:03.780
And after Noah's murder.
Darrell disappeared.

348
00:16:03.804 --> 00:16:04.864
Guy either died or went to ground.

349
00:16:04.888 --> 00:16:06.199
There's zero trace of him.

350
00:16:06.223 --> 00:16:08.368
If Darrell killed Noah.
the G-Parks knew.

351
00:16:08.392 --> 00:16:10.662
Hell. he'll be a dead man
if he didn't disappear.

352
00:16:10.686 --> 00:16:12.163
According to the Cook County docket.

353
00:16:12.187 --> 00:16:14.499
he's got an active bench
warrant for an old drug case.

354
00:16:14.523 --> 00:16:16.459
- Any known associates?
- No.

355
00:16:16.483 --> 00:16:18.169
- No family either.
- All right.

356
00:16:18.193 --> 00:16:19.253
Well. keep digging until you find

357
00:16:19.277 --> 00:16:20.421
someone who knows something.

358
00:16:20.445 --> 00:16:22.507
Wait. wait.

359
00:16:22.531 --> 00:16:24.050
He's got a cousin. Larry Moore.

360
00:16:24.074 --> 00:16:26.678
He's been dead four years.
but he's got water.

361
00:16:26.702 --> 00:16:28.346
gas. and electric bills in his name

362
00:16:28.370 --> 00:16:29.806
in a back unit apartment in Englewood.

363
00:16:29.830 --> 00:16:30.998
Go.

364
00:16:42.634 --> 00:16:44.779
Approaching the back unit now.

365
00:16:44.803 --> 00:16:46.364
Copy you. Front's secure.

366
00:17:01.403 --> 00:17:03.173
We got movement in the garage.

367
00:17:04.489 --> 00:17:05.489
Copy you.

368
00:17:09.536 --> 00:17:10.888
Chicago PD!

369
00:17:10.912 --> 00:17:12.515
Turn off the vehicle and get out.

370
00:17:12.539 --> 00:17:13.915
Turn it off!

371
00:17:17.002 --> 00:17:18.420
Hey. stop!

372
00:17:20.756 --> 00:17:22.066
Turn off the vehicle right now!

373
00:17:22.090 --> 00:17:23.258
Hands up!

374
00:17:25.510 --> 00:17:27.613
- Gun.
- Got it.

375
00:17:27.637 --> 00:17:29.162
Get out.

376
00:17:29.598 --> 00:17:31.075
Get down.

377
00:17:31.099 --> 00:17:32.035
You got anything that can hurt me?

378
00:17:32.059 --> 00:17:33.119
No.

379
00:17:33.143 --> 00:17:34.412
Get your hands behind your back.

380
00:17:34.436 --> 00:17:35.705
Hands behind your back. Don't move.

381
00:17:35.729 --> 00:17:36.706
I'm not fighting you.

382
00:17:36.730 --> 00:17:38.708
Just get me off of the street.

383
00:17:38.732 --> 00:17:39.917
He was all packed up

384
00:17:39.941 --> 00:17:41.085
like he knew you were coming. Ocean.

385
00:17:41.109 --> 00:17:42.378
I said. get me off the street!

386
00:17:42.402 --> 00:17:43.926
I heard you. Get up.

387
00:17:47.824 --> 00:17:49.177
- Get me off the street.
- What do you mean?

388
00:17:49.201 --> 00:17:50.762
- What are you talking about?
- Get me someplace safe.

389
00:17:50.786 --> 00:17:52.221
- Why?
- He's gonna kill me.

390
00:17:52.245 --> 00:17:53.890
Okay? Get me out of here.

391
00:17:53.914 --> 00:17:55.725
Wait. wait. wait. wait. who?

392
00:17:55.749 --> 00:17:58.353
I'm a dead man if y'all don't listen.

393
00:17:58.377 --> 00:18:00.271
He's gonna kill me.

394
00:18:00.295 --> 00:18:03.358
He's gonna kill me. Please. please.

395
00:18:03.382 --> 00:18:05.109
He's gonna kill me.

396
00:18:11.765 --> 00:18:13.409
All right. get out.

397
00:18:13.433 --> 00:18:14.476
Come on.

398
00:18:16.978 --> 00:18:18.230
Inside.

399
00:18:20.691 --> 00:18:21.709
All right.

400
00:18:21.733 --> 00:18:24.212
You got what you asked for. Now talk.

401
00:18:24.236 --> 00:18:25.880
- Who can come down here?
- Nobody.

402
00:18:25.904 --> 00:18:26.881
How do I know that's true?

403
00:18:26.905 --> 00:18:28.549
Because he's telling you.

404
00:18:28.573 --> 00:18:30.431
What is going on?

405
00:18:31.410 --> 00:18:33.096
You don't talk. we lead you
right back outside.

406
00:18:33.120 --> 00:18:34.555
I need a deal.

407
00:18:35.073 --> 00:18:36.408
For what?

408
00:18:37.332 --> 00:18:39.227
Ripping that G-Park truck six years ago?

409
00:18:39.251 --> 00:18:40.645
Killing Noah Lewis.
Simone Morgan. Carter Thomas?

410
00:18:40.669 --> 00:18:42.939
I didn't kill nobody.

411
00:18:42.963 --> 00:18:44.065
Now. why would we believe that?

412
00:18:44.089 --> 00:18:45.817
Because it's true.

413
00:18:45.841 --> 00:18:48.444
I ripped a couple of trucks.
yeah. but I didn't kill nobody.

414
00:18:48.468 --> 00:18:49.821
And I want a deal saying that.

415
00:18:49.845 --> 00:18:51.906
I want a deal that's gonna protect me.

416
00:18:52.063 --> 00:18:53.314
From who?

417
00:19:00.313 --> 00:19:01.708
Three people lost their lives.

418
00:19:01.732 --> 00:19:03.835
and you thought you were
about to lose yours.

419
00:19:03.859 --> 00:19:06.945
You're not safe until
we choose to protect you.

420
00:19:10.849 --> 00:19:12.306
Tell me who.

421
00:19:18.313 --> 00:19:19.814
Brian Foster.

422
00:19:21.877 --> 00:19:23.479
Detective Brian Foster?

423
00:19:23.503 --> 00:19:24.772
Yes.

424
00:19:27.049 --> 00:19:28.234
Don't look at me like that. all right?

425
00:19:28.258 --> 00:19:29.444
It's true.

426
00:19:29.865 --> 00:19:31.237
He was working Bronzeville.

427
00:19:31.261 --> 00:19:32.697
He busted me once.

428
00:19:32.721 --> 00:19:34.240
One thing led to another.

429
00:19:34.264 --> 00:19:36.367
and we was working together. all right?

430
00:19:36.391 --> 00:19:37.410
I knew what the trucks was holding.

431
00:19:37.434 --> 00:19:38.727
I knew the routes.

432
00:19:38.751 --> 00:19:40.038
I would tell Foster the when
and the where and...

433
00:19:40.062 --> 00:19:41.080
He'd rip them with you?

434
00:19:41.104 --> 00:19:42.582
Yes.

435
00:19:42.606 --> 00:19:44.584
He'd pull them over like a traffic stop.

436
00:19:44.608 --> 00:19:47.795
I would rip the dope. but it went wrong.

437
00:19:47.819 --> 00:19:49.464
All right? Kid fought back.

438
00:19:49.488 --> 00:19:51.239
I saw Foster shoot him down.

439
00:19:53.408 --> 00:19:54.640
Foster?

440
00:19:55.160 --> 00:19:57.018
I'm telling you the truth.

441
00:20:04.226 --> 00:20:07.768
I mean. he says he was tipped
off by a call from Foster

442
00:20:08.063 --> 00:20:10.041
45 minutes before we showed up.

443
00:20:10.065 --> 00:20:11.959
He says Foster didn't want him
talking to cops.

444
00:20:11.983 --> 00:20:14.212
is convinced Foster would have
eventually killed him

445
00:20:14.236 --> 00:20:15.926
after the heat died down.

446
00:20:16.696 --> 00:20:18.549
The number who called him was a burner?

447
00:20:18.573 --> 00:20:20.259
Yes. Burner is off now.

448
00:20:20.283 --> 00:20:22.136
so we can't confirm it was really him.

449
00:20:22.160 --> 00:20:24.889
but Darrell does sound legitimate.

450
00:20:24.913 --> 00:20:26.808
He also lived under
an alias for six years.

451
00:20:26.832 --> 00:20:28.392
so clearly he's good at lying.

452
00:20:28.416 --> 00:20:30.186
He's also a really bad
cooperating defendant

453
00:20:30.210 --> 00:20:31.771
with zero solid proof.

454
00:20:31.795 --> 00:20:33.314
Who just put himself
at the scene of a crime

455
00:20:33.338 --> 00:20:34.732
of armed robbery and a murder.

456
00:20:34.756 --> 00:20:36.150
It's the word of a convicted felon

457
00:20:36.174 --> 00:20:37.527
versus a Homicide detective.

458
00:20:37.551 --> 00:20:38.611
But it fits.

459
00:20:38.635 --> 00:20:39.612
It all fits.

460
00:20:39.636 --> 00:20:41.114
Simone was scared.

461
00:20:41.138 --> 00:20:42.156
She didn't tell her husband.

462
00:20:42.180 --> 00:20:43.241
She didn't go to work.

463
00:20:43.265 --> 00:20:45.368
She hung up on the police three times.

464
00:20:45.392 --> 00:20:47.374
Who would scare her more than a cop?

465
00:20:48.937 --> 00:20:51.124
Odell Morgan was framed... well...

466
00:20:51.148 --> 00:20:53.292
and it was a long-range shot
that killed Carter Thomas.

467
00:20:53.316 --> 00:20:55.378
Which could indicate police skill set.

468
00:20:55.402 --> 00:20:57.255
And it was Detective Brian Foster.

469
00:20:57.279 --> 00:20:59.465
the only cop that knew
that we had reopened the case.

470
00:20:59.489 --> 00:21:01.592
We're gonna need a hell
of a lot more than this.

471
00:21:01.616 --> 00:21:02.973
I'm sorry.

472
00:21:03.618 --> 00:21:05.768
All right. we can move forward. but...

473
00:21:06.663 --> 00:21:10.417
unless we get something
concrete. we move real quiet.

474
00:21:12.711 --> 00:21:15.398
All right. first thing. get
Darrell's statement on record.

475
00:21:15.422 --> 00:21:17.132
Dante.

476
00:21:18.550 --> 00:21:20.862
See if Dominique recognizes Foster.

477
00:21:20.886 --> 00:21:22.095
Hmm?

478
00:21:34.733 --> 00:21:36.002
Hey. Maria.

479
00:21:36.026 --> 00:21:37.628
Is Dominique here?

480
00:21:37.652 --> 00:21:39.237
Uh...

481
00:21:41.948 --> 00:21:43.472
Is everything okay?

482
00:21:51.875 --> 00:21:54.479
Sarge. I found her.

483
00:21:54.503 --> 00:21:56.588
She's okay. but stand by.

484
00:22:06.556 --> 00:22:07.933
Dominique?

485
00:22:09.893 --> 00:22:11.913
What are you doing here?

486
00:22:11.937 --> 00:22:13.790
How did you find me?

487
00:22:14.201 --> 00:22:16.630
You share your location
with your roommate.

488
00:22:38.129 --> 00:22:40.215
My dad used to take me here.

489
00:22:42.926 --> 00:22:44.719
He loved the boats.

490
00:22:48.348 --> 00:22:50.205
I don't even know why.

491
00:22:51.101 --> 00:22:52.686
I never asked him.

492
00:22:56.231 --> 00:22:59.877
Your dad used to work
with boats in the summer

493
00:22:59.901 --> 00:23:01.800
when he was 16.

494
00:23:02.571 --> 00:23:04.531
Maybe that's why he liked them.

495
00:23:06.783 --> 00:23:08.682
I didn't know that.

496
00:23:10.287 --> 00:23:12.890
I didn't know that about my own father.

497
00:23:12.914 --> 00:23:14.642
You didn't get the time to know him.

498
00:23:14.666 --> 00:23:16.710
I didn't wanna know.

499
00:23:18.461 --> 00:23:20.481
I hated him!

500
00:23:22.340 --> 00:23:25.695
For six years. I hated him.

501
00:23:32.684 --> 00:23:35.542
Nothing makes sense anymore.

502
00:23:36.897 --> 00:23:39.171
What I thought I knew

503
00:23:39.941 --> 00:23:44.279
about my parents and my life...

504
00:23:46.364 --> 00:23:48.700
None of it makes sense now.

505
00:23:50.869 --> 00:23:52.579
It's like up is down.

506
00:23:55.373 --> 00:23:56.392
I get that.

507
00:23:56.416 --> 00:23:58.627
How can you get that?

508
00:24:00.212 --> 00:24:01.272
I know what it feels like

509
00:24:01.296 --> 00:24:03.232
when nothing makes sense anymore.

510
00:24:13.809 --> 00:24:15.811
What am I supposed to do now?

511
00:24:18.814 --> 00:24:20.148
I don't know.

512
00:24:25.320 --> 00:24:26.655
What did you do?

513
00:24:29.825 --> 00:24:32.160
I met your dad.

514
00:24:37.082 --> 00:24:39.398
He never lost his faith.

515
00:24:40.043 --> 00:24:41.354
Never.

516
00:24:41.378 --> 00:24:43.152
No one believed him.

517
00:24:43.880 --> 00:24:47.801
but he just kept on going.

518
00:24:51.972 --> 00:24:53.598
So...

519
00:24:56.476 --> 00:24:59.126
I guess we keep on going.

520
00:25:14.828 --> 00:25:16.722
I didn't realize how hungry I was.

521
00:25:18.707 --> 00:25:20.518
Who taught you to cook?

522
00:25:20.542 --> 00:25:21.644
My mom.

523
00:25:21.668 --> 00:25:23.437
Mm.

524
00:25:23.461 --> 00:25:24.605
My mom liked to cook.

525
00:25:24.629 --> 00:25:26.298
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

526
00:25:28.758 --> 00:25:31.654
I mean. I did come here
earlier because I wanted to...

527
00:25:31.678 --> 00:25:33.406
Oh. God. you have something. don't you?

528
00:25:33.430 --> 00:25:35.032
Yeah.

529
00:25:35.056 --> 00:25:37.618
- And I just completely...
- No. no. It's okay.

530
00:25:37.642 --> 00:25:39.287
Is it all right if I show you something?

531
00:25:39.311 --> 00:25:40.788
Yeah. yeah.

532
00:25:40.812 --> 00:25:42.623
All right.

533
00:25:42.647 --> 00:25:45.150
Do you recognize anyone here?

534
00:25:50.071 --> 00:25:51.406
Mm...

535
00:26:00.790 --> 00:26:02.189
No.

536
00:26:03.251 --> 00:26:05.188
Sorry. I don't.

537
00:26:05.552 --> 00:26:06.904
Okay.

538
00:26:06.955 --> 00:26:08.290
It's okay.

539
00:26:20.185 --> 00:26:21.746
Hey. wait.

540
00:26:21.770 --> 00:26:23.335
He looks...

541
00:26:24.606 --> 00:26:27.043
he didn't have on the uniform. but...

542
00:26:27.067 --> 00:26:28.211
Who?

543
00:26:28.235 --> 00:26:31.214
I think this man. he was there.

544
00:26:33.532 --> 00:26:35.556
The night my mom died.

545
00:26:36.243 --> 00:26:39.434
She walked me to a friend's
house for a sleepover. and...

546
00:26:41.248 --> 00:26:43.059
I think he was there.

547
00:26:45.906 --> 00:26:47.438
She remembers him.

548
00:26:47.463 --> 00:26:48.710
He was outside her friend's house

549
00:26:48.734 --> 00:26:50.251
in plain clothes. watching her mom.

550
00:26:50.275 --> 00:26:51.627
Simone didn't see.

551
00:26:51.651 --> 00:26:52.962
And Dominique at the time.
she shrugged it off

552
00:26:52.986 --> 00:26:54.422
as him being a neighbor or something.

553
00:26:54.446 --> 00:26:57.550
but that was Foster ID'ing
Simone for the first time.

554
00:26:57.574 --> 00:26:59.051
He was following her.

555
00:26:59.075 --> 00:27:00.928
We did a cell tower dump. confirmed it.

556
00:27:00.952 --> 00:27:02.722
Brian Foster's phone was
there near the friend's house.

557
00:27:02.746 --> 00:27:04.056
turned off an hour later.

558
00:27:04.080 --> 00:27:06.559
And it was his RDO. He wasn't on shift.

559
00:27:06.583 --> 00:27:08.352
There was no good reason
for him to be in that area.

560
00:27:08.376 --> 00:27:09.687
Still a hell a lot of room in that.

561
00:27:09.711 --> 00:27:11.355
I got more.

562
00:27:11.379 --> 00:27:14.191
So Dominique also told me
that Foster was watching her

563
00:27:14.215 --> 00:27:17.236
from a vehicle... a nice one.
which makes no sense.

564
00:27:17.260 --> 00:27:19.697
because Foster was
a beat cop at the time.

565
00:27:19.721 --> 00:27:21.699
But I found this.

566
00:27:21.723 --> 00:27:24.452
He bought a Porsche. paid for it in cash

567
00:27:24.476 --> 00:27:27.580
in his cousin's name.
made all service appointments.

568
00:27:27.604 --> 00:27:29.874
That's a $75.000 car.

569
00:27:29.898 --> 00:27:31.918
Foster didn't make that cash
from pushing a beat car.

570
00:27:31.942 --> 00:27:34.216
That cash was from drug rips.

571
00:27:37.155 --> 00:27:38.799
All right. do we have anything else?

572
00:27:38.823 --> 00:27:40.718
We did confirm Darrell's alibis

573
00:27:40.742 --> 00:27:42.678
for Simone and Carter's murders.

574
00:27:42.702 --> 00:27:44.680
We also confirmed that
he was arrested by Foster

575
00:27:44.704 --> 00:27:46.474
eight months prior to Noah's homicide.

576
00:27:46.498 --> 00:27:48.059
released without charges.

577
00:27:48.083 --> 00:27:50.478
Darrell's claims about
the drug rips do seem legit.

578
00:27:50.502 --> 00:27:52.229
but we don't have anything tangible

579
00:27:52.253 --> 00:27:55.441
that ties Foster to the crimes
other than Darrell's word.

580
00:27:55.465 --> 00:27:57.026
You get Dominique on record?

581
00:27:57.050 --> 00:27:58.050
Yes.

582
00:28:00.261 --> 00:28:01.572
That's enough to hold.

583
00:28:01.596 --> 00:28:03.908
but you're gonna have to build more.

584
00:28:03.932 --> 00:28:05.141
Yeah. we will.

585
00:28:09.980 --> 00:28:11.079
Okay.

586
00:28:11.103 --> 00:28:12.583
Bring him in.

587
00:28:12.607 --> 00:28:13.839
Hey.

588
00:28:14.856 --> 00:28:16.441
Move smart.

589
00:28:31.960 --> 00:28:33.567
Detective Foster.

590
00:28:34.838 --> 00:28:38.150
Hey. Officer Imani. Torres.

591
00:28:38.174 --> 00:28:39.652
You got a few minutes?

592
00:28:39.676 --> 00:28:42.446
Uh. sorry. Been a day.

593
00:28:42.470 --> 00:28:43.864
Any questions about your cold case

594
00:28:43.888 --> 00:28:45.491
are gonna have to wait.

595
00:28:45.515 --> 00:28:47.368
We understand. but we got something

596
00:28:47.392 --> 00:28:49.078
we need you to look at.

597
00:28:49.102 --> 00:28:50.621
We really would appreciate
your help on this.

598
00:28:50.645 --> 00:28:52.022
It won't take long.

599
00:28:55.442 --> 00:28:58.045
Really. now's not a good time.

600
00:28:58.069 --> 00:29:01.239
You're welcome to come back
tomorrow. okay?

601
00:29:10.624 --> 00:29:12.310
It's just a few questions.

602
00:29:24.220 --> 00:29:27.015
We'd really appreciate
your cooperation. Detective.

603
00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:32.042
Sure.

604
00:29:33.355 --> 00:29:35.106
You got it.

605
00:29:37.484 --> 00:29:40.212
We have evidence
corroborating our timeline.

606
00:29:40.236 --> 00:29:43.090
placing you at the scene
with each of our victims

607
00:29:43.114 --> 00:29:46.139
on or about the time of their murders.

608
00:29:46.534 --> 00:29:49.847
We have witness testimony
establishing your prior contact

609
00:29:49.871 --> 00:29:52.099
with Simone Morgan.

610
00:29:52.123 --> 00:29:54.518
And we have a witness who will testify

611
00:29:54.542 --> 00:29:57.229
that you were at the scene
of Noah Lewis's death.

612
00:29:57.253 --> 00:29:59.941
that you shot and killed him.

613
00:29:59.965 --> 00:30:01.275
and that you had motive to kill

614
00:30:01.299 --> 00:30:04.278
both Simone Morgan and Carter Thomas.

615
00:30:04.302 --> 00:30:05.971
That's three homicides.

616
00:30:10.016 --> 00:30:12.936
The sooner you talk.
the better your chances.

617
00:30:16.273 --> 00:30:17.754
That's all?

618
00:30:19.901 --> 00:30:21.796
This is ridiculous.

619
00:30:21.820 --> 00:30:23.844
You don't have enough to charge.

620
00:30:25.198 --> 00:30:28.640
So I'll just make myself
comfortable right here.

621
00:30:29.494 --> 00:30:31.518
That okay with you two?

622
00:30:33.165 --> 00:30:35.125
Go right ahead.

623
00:30:47.387 --> 00:30:49.764
Odell Morgan was
a good man. a smart man.

624
00:30:52.038 --> 00:30:53.498
He didn't give up.

625
00:30:54.102 --> 00:30:55.792
And I won't either.

626
00:33:00.812 --> 00:33:02.540
- I got him.
- Good morning.

627
00:33:02.564 --> 00:33:04.417
There was a rug missing
from Morgan's living room.

628
00:33:04.441 --> 00:33:05.372
Okay.

629
00:33:05.396 --> 00:33:07.003
And the false witness. Carter. claimed

630
00:33:07.027 --> 00:33:08.337
he saw Odell carrying
the rug out to his car.

631
00:33:08.361 --> 00:33:10.089
We know that's a lie. but...

632
00:33:10.113 --> 00:33:11.966
The best lies are closest to the truth.

633
00:33:11.990 --> 00:33:14.468
So Foster would have needed
a vehicle to transport the rug

634
00:33:14.492 --> 00:33:16.053
and Simone's body out of the house.

635
00:33:16.077 --> 00:33:17.763
and he wouldn't have used
his police squad.

636
00:33:17.787 --> 00:33:19.098
He would have used his personal vehicle.

637
00:33:19.122 --> 00:33:20.600
And both of Foster's
vehicles at the time

638
00:33:20.624 --> 00:33:21.976
were two-door coupes.

639
00:33:22.000 --> 00:33:23.477
A rug wouldn't have fit inside.

640
00:33:23.501 --> 00:33:25.187
- So he borrowed another.
- He had to.

641
00:33:25.211 --> 00:33:26.731
But you wouldn't borrow
a friend's car for that.

642
00:33:26.755 --> 00:33:28.608
You wouldn't steal one. That's too hot.

643
00:33:28.632 --> 00:33:30.985
So I ran through all
of Foster's traffic stops

644
00:33:31.009 --> 00:33:32.945
that resulted in impound. and I found

645
00:33:32.969 --> 00:33:35.489
a gray Chevy pickup truck that
was scheduled to be destroyed.

646
00:33:35.513 --> 00:33:37.245
- Was it?
- No.

647
00:33:37.974 --> 00:33:40.119
That same Chevy pickup truck
was found missing

648
00:33:40.143 --> 00:33:41.662
the day after Simone's murder.

649
00:33:41.686 --> 00:33:44.040
There's no way that's a coincidence.

650
00:33:44.064 --> 00:33:46.483
Foster used that truck to dump the body.

651
00:33:47.651 --> 00:33:49.170
That's good work. Dante.

652
00:33:50.862 --> 00:33:52.173
Call in the team.

653
00:33:57.400 --> 00:33:58.795
This was six years ago.

654
00:33:58.853 --> 00:34:00.267
The only traffic cams we have are what

655
00:34:00.290 --> 00:34:01.808
the lead detective saved.
and it's not a lot.

656
00:34:01.831 --> 00:34:03.358
Then we run historical
on all plate readers.

657
00:34:03.382 --> 00:34:04.733
- Is that saved?
- It should be.

658
00:34:04.757 --> 00:34:06.614
I got multiple hits on that
vehicle prior to that day.

659
00:34:06.638 --> 00:34:08.242
I got it.

660
00:34:08.265 --> 00:34:09.659
I got the Chevy going through
two different toll booths

661
00:34:09.683 --> 00:34:11.161
and an exit the night of the murder.

662
00:34:11.185 --> 00:34:12.454
And timeline matches.

663
00:34:12.478 --> 00:34:13.955
I got it around Wilmette.

664
00:34:13.979 --> 00:34:15.248
Check for a nexus.

665
00:34:15.272 --> 00:34:16.625
Wilmette and Brian Foster.

666
00:34:16.649 --> 00:34:17.733
Copy you.

667
00:34:19.485 --> 00:34:21.379
Yeah. I got nothing that ties him yet.

668
00:34:21.403 --> 00:34:22.464
The lake's out there.

669
00:34:22.488 --> 00:34:23.799
There's inlets. pockets.

670
00:34:23.823 --> 00:34:25.204
Enough to dump a body and a car?

671
00:34:25.228 --> 00:34:26.259
Possible.

672
00:34:26.283 --> 00:34:28.804
That's a damn good way
to make them disappear.

673
00:34:28.828 --> 00:34:30.097
Simone's there.

674
00:34:30.121 --> 00:34:31.306
- She's there.
- All right.

675
00:34:31.330 --> 00:34:32.599
What was the last hit on the toll booth?

676
00:34:32.623 --> 00:34:34.142
What exit?

677
00:34:34.166 --> 00:34:35.352
I got it.

678
00:34:35.376 --> 00:34:36.550
Dempster Road.

679
00:34:36.574 --> 00:34:38.067
Let's hit it.

680
00:35:46.155 --> 00:35:48.012
What are the chances...

681
00:35:50.075 --> 00:35:52.766
my van hits a police car this morning?

682
00:35:53.412 --> 00:35:55.515
Your car.

683
00:35:55.539 --> 00:35:58.226
What are the damn chances?

684
00:35:58.250 --> 00:36:00.228
Your car.

685
00:36:00.252 --> 00:36:02.814
It's fate?

686
00:36:02.838 --> 00:36:05.275
What else could it be?

687
00:36:11.305 --> 00:36:13.658
1070 to 5021 units.

688
00:36:13.682 --> 00:36:16.286
We got something
between 87th Street point

689
00:36:16.310 --> 00:36:17.329
and the breaker wall.

690
00:36:17.353 --> 00:36:18.455
Deploying divers now.

691
00:38:48.587 --> 00:38:51.233
Hey. my 48 must be up.

692
00:38:51.257 --> 00:38:52.484
If you have any more questions...

693
00:38:52.508 --> 00:38:54.653
Brian Foster. you're under arrest

694
00:38:54.677 --> 00:38:57.781
for the murders of Simone
Morgan and Noah Lewis.

695
00:38:57.805 --> 00:38:58.990
What?

696
00:38:59.014 --> 00:39:00.408
You have the right to remain silent.

697
00:39:00.432 --> 00:39:02.869
Anything you say can
and will be used against you

698
00:39:02.893 --> 00:39:04.417
in a court of law.

699
00:39:04.441 --> 00:39:06.623
What are you talking about?
You don't have anything on me.

700
00:39:06.647 --> 00:39:07.999
We have Simone's body.

701
00:39:08.023 --> 00:39:09.835
You have the right to an attorney.

702
00:39:10.130 --> 00:39:12.003
If you cannot afford an attorney.

703
00:39:12.027 --> 00:39:14.381
one will be provided for you.

704
00:39:14.405 --> 00:39:18.009
Do you understand these rights
as I have told them to you?
